 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-title field-type-ds field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;dc:title&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;ChildrenOfSyria.info&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;The conflict in Syria has entered its fifth brutal year. UNICEF estimates some 14 million children are now affected in Syria and in neighboring countries. In this new web site, ChildrenOfSyria.info, UNICEF tells the stories of many children living through this horror. Through their eyes, we see their homes bombed, their loved ones lost, and their education stripped.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But &lt;a href=&quot;http://ChildrenOfSyria.info&quot;&gt;ChildrenOfSyria.info&lt;/a&gt; is not just retelling stories of despair. On the contrary, the children featured in the site are courageous and determined to create a better life for themselves and others in this crisis. It’s about hope and action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can take action, too: share your word of encouragement or make a donation via &lt;a href=&quot;http://ChildrenOfSyria.info&quot;&gt;ChildrenOfSyria.info&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
